finding: High expression of nsp2, nsp5, nsp10, nsp15, and nsp16 in HEK293/ACE2 cells.
Purification of SARS-CoV nsp-containing complexes using a bio-tag and streptavidin beads.
Identification of candidate host proteins copurifying with SARS-CoV nsp2 through mudpit analysis and western blotting.
Confirmation of interaction between SARS-CoV nsp2 and host proteins PHB1 and PHB2 through western blotting.

PHB1 and PHB2 are evolutionarily conserved proteins involved in cellular functions such as cell cycle progression, cell migration, cellular differentiation, apoptosis, and mitochondrial biogenesis, suggesting a role for nsp2 in altering the host cell environment.
